<title>Throwing stones at locusts</title>
<summary><i>The locusts (with the locust birds which accompany them) are set free by Sorcerers. Stones not to be thrown at the locusts. (L V.-21. 5708-5719 1/2) (L VIII.-31. 8754-8758).</i> |han≠kass&apos;o and ||hoaken !khe were told by |han≠kass&apos;o&apos;s grandfather not to throw stones at locusts. A second part of the story concerns |kaunu who says &apos;locusts come out&apos; when he wants to drive the locusts with the children.</summary><comments>1) p.8756v: the locust bird and the locusts, 2) See also <i>Locust birds </i>and<i> The locust bird or ||kerri</i>, 3) This story is found in Book VIII-31</comments><date>August 1879</date><storypages>8754-8758</storypages><category>History (personal)</category><category>Plants and animals</category><category>Custom and daily life</category><author>|han≠kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>locusts</kw><subkw>and the locust bird</subkw></keyword>
